Sen. Kabiru Ibrahim Gaya has distributed 110 laptop computers to youths from the eight local government in Kano South Senatorial District who underwent ICT training. Speaking during the graduation and distribution of computers held at the Industrial Training Fund (ITF) in Kano, Sen. Gaya, represented by Alhaji Abdulhamid Idris, said the empowerment programme was targeted at youths and women towards self-reliance. In his remark, Malam Umar Ibrahim Auta who is ITF’s Deputy Director and Training Manager, Industrial Skills Training Centre, Kano, urged well-meaning politicians and political office holders to emulate Sen. Gaya. Gaya, Jibrin retain senatorial seats Inside Kano’s neglected youth centre Kano APC senatorial primaries: Sen. Gaya, Sumaila sign peace pact Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin